<task id="AIPU2-079" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build ConversationPane Wrapping SprkChat as Child</title>
    <phase>4B</phase>
    <tags>frontend, conversation, sprkchat</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-075, AIPU2-076</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    R1's ChatPanel.tsx was the top-level host for SprkChat, managing auth, session init, and
    SSE streaming directly. In R2, AiSessionProvider (AIPU2-076) takes over session and
    streaming concerns; ConversationPane is a thin wrapper that renders SprkChat as a child
    and bridges SprkChat's onPaneEvent callback to PaneEventBus dispatch. SprkChat's existing
    prop interface must be preserved — no changes to the SprkChat component itself. ConversationPane
    also manages the Welcome → ActiveChat stage transition within the conversation slot.
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with React 19 component composition and Fluent v9 experience.</role>
  <goal>
    SprkChat renders inside ConversationPane with all R1 functionality intact. SprkChat's
    onPaneEvent events flow to PaneEventBus. Welcome → ActiveChat transition handled.
    R1's ChatPanel.tsx is replaced.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ChatPanel.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read ChatPanel.tsx and SprkChat.tsx to understand the current SprkChat props interface (especially onPaneEvent, session props, streaming props) and what ChatPanel currently manages.</step>
    <step>Create src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx.</step>
    <step>Wire SprkChat's session and streaming props from useAiSession() hook (from AiSessionProvider) — do not pass raw auth tokens or SSE hooks directly from ConversationPane.</step>
    <step>Implement the onPaneEvent callback: receive the SprkChatPaneEvent from SprkChat, map it to the appropriate PaneEventBus channel and dispatch it using useDispatchPaneEvent().</step>
    <step>Implement Welcome stage: when ShellStage is 'welcome', render a Fluent v9 welcome UI above or instead of SprkChat input; transition to 'active-chat' when the user sends the first message.</step>
    <step>Ensure SprkChat.tsx receives the same prop values it received from ChatPanel.tsx — no regressions in R1 SprkChat functionality.</step>
    <step>Place ConversationPane in the conversation slot of ThreePaneShell (replace placeholder div).</step>
    <step>Verify the full chat flow works end-to-end: user types → SprkChat sends → SSE received by AiSessionProvider → dispatched to PaneEventBus → WorkspacePane and ContextPaneController both update.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>ConversationPane renders SprkChat as a child component with preserved prop interface.</criterion>
    <criterion>SprkChat's onPaneEvent events dispatch to the correct PaneEventBus channel.</criterion>
    <criterion>Session and streaming state wired from useAiSession(), not duplicated in ConversationPane.</criterion>
    <criterion>Welcome stage renders before first message; transitions to active-chat on first send.</criterion>
    <criterion>R1's ChatPanel.tsx is replaced by ConversationPane.</criterion>
    <criterion>End-to-end chat flow (user input → SSE → all three panes update) works correctly.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
